<div style="padding:2rem;font-family:monospace;max-width:700px;background:#0d0d0d;min-height:100vh;color:#ccc">
  <a href="/" style="color:#888;font-size:0.85rem">← Back to index</a>
  <h1 style="color:#fff;margin:0.5rem 0 0.25rem">Multi-Param — /shop/:category/:productId</h1>
  <p style="color:#888;margin-bottom:1.5rem">
    Both <code>params.category</code> and <code>params.productId</code> are decoded independently.
    Either can contain traversal payloads. They are concatenated into the fetch URL.
    Try: <a href="/shop/..%2Fadmin/99" style="color:#f44">/shop/..%2Fadmin/99</a>
  </p>

  <div style="background:#1a1a1a;border:1px solid #333;border-radius:6px;padding:1rem;margin-bottom:1rem">
    <div style="color:#888;font-size:0.8rem;margin-bottom:4px">SOURCE</div>
    <code style="color:#f90">params.category + params.productId → fetch(`/api/shop/$&lbrace;category&rbrace;/products/$&lbrace;productId&rbrace;`)</code>
  </div>

  <div style="background:#1a1a1a;border:1px solid {{if @model.hasTraversal '#f44' '#555'}};border-radius:6px;padding:1rem;margin-bottom:1rem">
    <div style="color:#888;font-size:0.8rem;margin-bottom:4px">RAW VALUES</div>
    <code style="color:{{if @model.hasTraversal '#f44' '#ccc'}};font-size:1.1rem">
      category = "{{@model.rawCategory}}"
    </code><br/>
    <code style="color:{{if @model.hasTraversal '#f44' '#ccc'}};font-size:1.1rem">
      productId = "{{@model.rawProductId}}"
    </code>
    <div style="color:{{if @model.hasTraversal '#f44' '#888'}};font-size:0.8rem;margin-top:8px">
      {{#if @model.hasTraversal}}
        DANGEROUS: Traversal in one or both params — combined URL enables path escape
      {{else}}
        Normal values
      {{/if}}
    </div>
  </div>

  <div style="background:#1a1a1a;border:1px solid {{if @model.hasTraversal '#f44' '#555'}};border-radius:6px;padding:1rem;margin-bottom:1rem">
    <div style="color:#888;font-size:0.8rem;margin-bottom:4px">FETCH URL CONSTRUCTED</div>
    <code style="color:{{if @model.hasTraversal '#f44' '#ccc'}};font-size:1rem">{{@model.fetchUrl}}</code>
  </div>

  <div style="background:#1a1a1a;border:1px solid #555;border-radius:6px;padding:1rem">
    <div style="color:#888;font-size:0.8rem;margin-bottom:4px">RESULT from fetch</div>
    <pre style="margin:0;color:#ccc;white-space:pre-wrap">{{json @model.result}}</pre>
  </div>
</div>
